@JeffreyRichter @mikekistler could you help approve the api breaking change here? which I think should be false alarms. 
This PR is trying to split ContainerRegistry service into two services as ContainerRegistry and ContainerRegistryTasks in order to resolve the version uniform issue. It doesn't change any real API contract here other than moving files and change the file references according to the guideline. 

Let me know if you have any concerns, thank you!

RegistryTasks is a split service from container registry, so all the opeartion group need a parent parameter in paths.
Don't know if I can use this way to add it in path parameter.
 for example, swagger:
```
"/subscriptions/{subscriptionId}/resourceGroups/{resourceGroupName}/providers/Microsoft.ContainerRegistry/registries/{registryName}/tasks": {
      "get": {
        "operationId": "Tasks_List",
        "tags": [
          "Tasks"
        ],
        "description": "Lists all the tas

Sorry for my mistake of introducing breaking changes when doing typespec conversion.
@mcgallan and I have double confirmed the differences between origin swagger and the generated swagger.
There's no additional properties being added into the stable version.

@kazrael2119 Thanks for catching this! We do need this example for Registries_Create:
```
          "RegistryCreateAbac": {
            "$ref": "./examples/RegistryCreateAbac.json"
          }
```
I missed including this example in the Swagger file previously

@northtyphoon I discussed with @jaysterp in a meeting and we agreed on the path forward. I sign off on the PR as long as the parameter names and param data type/values are:
* `regionalEndpoints: enum { "Enabled", "Disabled" }`
* `endpointProtocolVersion: enum { "IPv4Only", "IPv4AndIPv6" }`

@mentat9 Can you override the two failing required CIs (Swagger LintDiff and TypeSpec Validation)?

Regarding Swagger LintDiff - those all appear to be false positives, as it's comparing the new API version to the last API version (a GA version) instead of the last preview API version.

Regarding TypeSpec validation - I implemented the fixes for this API version, but the CI is also including files that are not being touched in this PR.

I'd hoped that we can add instructions to let agent add convenience code automatically (at least for resources that already have such).

Live test may be a harder problem. (there are more and more restrictions on Playground subscription)

@XiaofeiCao
